<div class="item-content">
<h3><a href="https://calwatchdog.com/2015/04/26/tech-turns-from-sf-to-la/">Tech turns from SF to LA</a></h3>
<p>Looking for greener pastures and fresher stomping grounds, California&#8217;s top tech players have started a virtual stampede toward Los Angeles.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="item-block">
<div class="item-header">
<a href="https://calwatchdog.com/2016/10/12/secure-choice-state-run-retirement-plan-guarantee-taxpayer-bailouts/#comments" class="item-comment"><span>5</span><i></i></a>
<a href="https://calwatchdog.com/category/budget-and-finance/" class="item-category">Budget and Finance</a>
<a href="https://calwatchdog.com/2016/10/" class="item-date">
<i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i>
3 years ago </a>
<a href="https://calwatchdog.com/2016/10/12/secure-choice-state-run-retirement-plan-guarantee-taxpayer-bailouts/" class="item-photo">
<img src="https://calwatchdog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/pension-retirement-374x200_c.jpg" alt="Does the Secure Choice state-run retirement plan guarantee against taxpayer bailouts?" /> </a>
</div>
<div class="item-content">
<h3><a href="https://calwatchdog.com/2016/10/12/secure-choice-state-run-retirement-plan-guarantee-taxpayer-bailouts/">Does the Secure Choice state-run retirement plan guarantee against taxpayer bailouts?</a></h3>
<p>Arguably the biggest selling point for Secure Choice &#8212; the state-run, automatic retirement account measure signed into law last month &#8212;</p>
